Prerequisites
Make sure you have the following installed:

Node.js (v16 or higher recommended)

npm (comes with Node.js)

Git

Project Setup
1. Clone the Repository
Open your terminal and run:

git clone https://github.com/Namratathale/VyaparAI.git
cd VyaparAI
2. Setup Frontend
cd vyapar-ai
npm install
npm start
The frontend usually runs on http://localhost:3000.

If the port is occupied, you can change it in the package.json or when prompted.

3. Setup Backend
Open a new terminal window/tab and run:

cd vyapar-server
npm install
npm start
The backend usually runs on http://localhost:5000.

Ensure the frontend and backend ports match your environment configuration.

Running the Application
Start the backend server first (vyapar-server).

Start the frontend (vyapar-ai).

Access the application in your browser at http://localhost:3000.

Updating the Project
To pull the latest changes from the repository:

git pull origin main
After pulling updates, you may need to reinstall packages if package.json changed:

npm install
Folder Structure
VyaparAI/
│
├── vyapar-ai/         # Frontend code
│   ├── public/
│   └── src/
│
├── vyapar-server/     # Backend code
│   ├── controllers/
│   ├── models/
│   └── routes/
│
├── README.md          # Project documentation
└── package.json       # Project metadata
